lash - lacking ambition shell
-----------------------------

 _           _
| | __ _ ___| |__
| |/ _` / __| '_ \
| | (_| \__ \ | | |
|_|\__,_|___/_| |_|


Simple featureless shell (without POSIX compatibility) written for fun and
eductational purposes.

Goals
-----
1) simplicity and understandability.
2) extensibility.

Not goals
---------
1) POSIX compatibility is encouraged, but if the feature adds unnecessary
complexity it should be redesigned.
2) Features for interactive usage are not in priority.

Installation
------------
Enter the following command to build and install lash (if necessary as root):
	make install

Usage
-----
To run lash in interactive mode enter the following:
	lash

To execute your script enter:
	lash yourscript.sh

You can check example scripts from "examples" directory.

Implemented POSIX shell operations
----------------------
1) Token recognition.
2) Simple command execution.
3) (&&, ||, |, &) Lists execution.
4) stdin and stdout redirection.
5) Builtins execution.
6) Foreground and background (partially. See
  https://www.gnu.org/software/libc/manual/html_node/Implementing-a-Shell.html
  for more info).
7) Comments
8) Scripts execution.

List of builtin commands
-------------------------
exit, cd.

